urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.

urlText: Wynyard Station, temporary bus stop closure
content:
From 3am to 6am on Saturday 12 June and Sunday 13 June 2021, Crane works on the Sydney Harbour Bridge will result in the following bus stop closures and diversions for bus services heading southbound on the bridge:
  • Bus stop Wynyard Station, York St, Stand M (200035) will be closed and missed by the 607X and 607N services towards the City QVB. The 607X and 607N will use the Sydney Harbour Tunnel instead of the Sydney Harbour Bridge and end at the QVB, York St, Stand E (2000136) as per usual.
  • Bus stop Wynyard Station, York St, Stand K (200033) will be closed and missed by the N90 and N92 services towards the City Town Hall. The N90 and N92 will use the Sydney Harbour Tunnel instead of the Sydney Harbour Bridge and end at Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand K (2000252).
Customers on the above services who need to get back to Wynyard Station can catch the BN1 service from bus stop QVB, Stand B (200042) to Wynyard Station, Carrington St, Stand B (200023) or they can walk from York St/Park St towards Wynyard Station.
subtitle: Wynyard Station, temporary bus stop closure
